        <div class = "aboutme__div">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Anthony holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science & Software Development from DePaul University. His expertise encompasses web application development, 
                with hands-on experience in various frameworks, including Flask and Rocket.Dedicated to continually enhancing his skills, Anthony is committed to developing object-oriented programs that offer 
                user-friendly experiences.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;He is currently on the lookout for entry-level developer positions where he can flourish and gain knowledge under expert guidance and mentorship. Among his notable projects
                is "Jeffsite," a Healthcare Database Management system initiated in September 2023. This project aims to streamline balance sheet management for healthcare providers, boasting a user-friendly
                interface coupled with an integrated feedback system for efficient change monitoring. 
            </p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Anthony is also passionate about language learning. In December 2022, he embarked on creating a Flash Card web
                app that allows users to generate and assess digital flashcard collections spanning a variety of topics. The app leverages Rust's memory efficiency to provide a well-organized management system and optimized data storage.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Residing in Chicago, Anthony contributes part-time as an assistant to a senior resident at Artis Assisted Living Facility. In this role, he offers support with in-room mobility and engages in 
                daily neighborhood walks, fostering a relationship built on respect and camaraderie.
            </p>
